text: Workday has been building
and shipping machine learning features
for nearly a decade.

Machine learning is at
the core of our platform.

We rely on AWS to provide
the compute at scale,
the infrastructure at global availability,

and a team of experts who
understand our technology
and our business to help solve problems.

Recently we announced a number
of generative AI features.

We worked closely with AWS to
help develop some of those.
We use tools like AWS SageMaker,
the Notebooks and JumpStart.

Those tools help us really
quickly identify experiments,
evaluate different options,
and then take them to production.

Recently we were working
with the SageMaker team
and improved latency

on our large language
model inference by 5x.

The tools that AWS provides
not only help us deliver that

in a global manner to
our global customer base,

but also do that in a way that
meets our complex security
and data privacy requirements,
and it provides a team of experts
who's available to us 24/7,
who understand the technology that we use,
and not only provide support,

but continuously innovates
to help partner with us

to make those features come
to life for our customers.
